definition.name: Claims

fields.name: id
fields.description: Unique claim identifier (UUID format)

fields.name: memberId
fields.description: Reference to the member (patient) who received the service. Links to members table.

fields.name: providerId
fields.description: Reference to the healthcare provider who performed the service. Links to provider_records table.

fields.name: dos
fields.description:
Date of Service - when the medical service was actually performed.
Format: YYYY-MM-DD. Used for eligibility checks and timely filing requirements.

fields.name: cpt
fields.description:
Current Procedural Terminology code - standardized 5-digit code for medical procedures.
Examples: 99213 (office visit), 70450 (CT scan head), 80053 (metabolic panel).
Used for billing and determining allowed amounts. Each CPT has an associated fee schedule.

fields.name: status
fields.description:
Claim processing status. Three possible values:
- PAID: Claim was approved and payment processed to provider
- DENIED: Claim was rejected (see denialReason for why)
- PENDING: Claim is under review, awaiting adjudication decision

fields.name: chargeCents
fields.description:
Amount charged by the provider in cents (divide by 100 for dollars).
This is what the provider billed, not necessarily what gets paid.
Example: 125000 = $1,250.00. Always >= allowedCents.

fields.name: allowedCents
fields.description:
Amount allowed/approved by the insurance plan in cents (divide by 100 for dollars).
This is what the insurance will actually pay according to the fee schedule.
Zero if claim was denied. Always <= chargeCents.
The difference (chargeCents - allowedCents) may be billed to the member.

fields.name: denialReason
fields.description:
Reason the claim was denied (only populated when status is DENIED).
Common reasons in this dataset:
- "Prior authorization required" - Service needed pre-approval
- "Out of network provider" - Provider not in plan network
- "Service not covered" - Procedure not included in plan benefits
- "Medical necessity not established" - Clinical justification insufficient
- "Duplicate claim" - Already paid for this service/date

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: Timestamp when the claim was first submitted to the system

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: Timestamp when the claim was last modified (status change, resubmission, etc.)

definition.description:
Medical claims submitted for healthcare services. Each claim represents a request
for payment from a healthcare provider for services rendered to a member. Claims
can be PAID (approved), DENIED (rejected), or PENDING (under review). The charge
amount is what the provider billed, while the allowed amount is what the insurance
plan approved for payment. Common denial reasons include lack of prior authorization,
out-of-network providers, or services not covered by the member's plan.

definition.name: Members

fields.name: id
fields.description: Unique member identifier (UUID format)

fields.name: firstName
fields.description: Member's legal first name

fields.name: lastName
fields.description: Member's legal last name

fields.name: dob
fields.description:
Date of birth in YYYY-MM-DD format. Used for eligibility verification,
age-based coverage rules, and dependent eligibility. Patients under 26
may be on parent's plan, over 65 qualify for Medicare.

fields.name: plan
fields.description:
Insurance plan type (HMO, PPO, EPO, POS, or HDHP).
- HMO: Requires in-network providers and PCP selection
- PPO: Allows out-of-network at higher cost
- EPO: In-network only except emergencies
Plan type affects coverage, cost-sharing, and claim approval.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: Timestamp when member record was first created in the system

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: Timestamp when member record was last updated

definition.description:
Insurance plan members (patients) enrolled in healthcare coverage.
Members can have multiple claims and eligibility checks.

definition.name: ProviderRecords

fields.name: id
fields.description: Unique provider identifier (UUID format)

fields.name: npi
fields.description:
National Provider Identifier - unique 10-digit identifier for US healthcare providers.
Required for all HIPAA-compliant transactions. Example: 1234567890.
NPIs are issued by CMS and never change.

fields.name: name
fields.description:
Provider's full name (for individuals) or facility name (for organizations).
Examples: "Dr. Sarah Johnson", "City General Hospital", "Main Street Clinic"

fields.name: specialty
fields.description:
Medical specialty or practice area. Common specialties:
- Cardiology (heart and cardiovascular system)
- Orthopedic Surgery (bones, joints, muscles)
- Family Medicine (primary care for all ages)
- Radiology (medical imaging)
- Internal Medicine (adult primary care)
Specialty affects fee schedules and authorization requirements.

fields.name: createdAt
fields.description: Timestamp when provider was added to the system

fields.name: updatedAt
fields.description: Timestamp when provider record was last updated

definition.description:
Healthcare providers (doctors, hospitals, clinics) who submit claims.
Each provider has a unique National Provider Identifier (NPI).

definition.name: ProviderRecords
definition.description: Legacy provider records from Hasura. Use federated Provider type for new queries.

charge_cents.description: Amount charged by provider in cents

denial_reason.description: Reason for claim denial (required when status is DENIED)
